x^y(a) Function
	If previous result != null:
    x = previous result
  Else
    x = 0
    
  Call Function pow(a, x)
		If a is negative:
			If x is integer:
				If x is even:
					Return pow(-a, x)
				Else x is odd:
					Return -1 * pow(-a, x)
				End if
			Else x is not integer:
				Log error: unreal solution
			End if
		Else if x is negative:
			Return 1 / pow(a, -x)
		End if
		If exponent is greater than 1:
			Return (pow(a, x/2))^2
		Else:
			Apply Newtonâ€™s method to solve fractional exponent
      (precision can be set separately)
	End function
